tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE sensor_data (
   sensor_id INT,
   sensor_type VARCHAR(255),
   timestamp TIMESTAMP,
   temperature FLOAT,
   humidity FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE sensors_data_source_1 (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    temperature FLOAT,
    humidity FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE sensors_data_source_2 (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    pressure FLOAT,
    airflow FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE combined_sensor_data (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    temperature FLOAT,
    humidity FLOAT,
    pressure FLOAT,
    airflow FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE sensor_data_1 (
    sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    temperature DECIMAL(10,2),
    humidity DECIMAL(10,2),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE sensor_data_2 (
    sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    pressure DECIMAL(10,2),
    altitude DECIMAL(10,2),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE sensor_metadata (
    sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    location VARCHAR(100),
    owner VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE sensor_analytics (
    sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    anomaly_score DECIMAL(10,2),
    analysis_result VARCHAR(100),
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE sensors_data_source1 (
    sensor_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    sensor_name VARCHAR(255),
    sensor_type VARCHAR(100),
    data_value FLOAT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);
